      "question": "If the probability of an event $E$ is $\\frac{3}{7}$, what is the probability of the event 'not $E$'?",
      "answer": "$\\frac{4}{7}$",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Recall that for any event E, P(not E) = 1 - P(E).",
          "Substitute P(E) = 3/7.",
          "Calculate: 1 - 3/7 = 4/7."
        ],
        "derivation": "P(not E) = 1 - P(E) = 1 - \\frac{3}{7} = \\frac{4}{7}"
      },
