    {
      "question": "A bag contains 5 red balls and some blue balls. If the probability of drawing a blue ball is twice that of drawing a red ball, find the number of blue balls in the bag.",
      "answer": "10",
      "solution": {
        "steps": [
          "Let the number of blue balls be x.",
          "Total balls = 5 + x.",
          "P(red) = 5/(5+x), P(blue) = x/(5+x).",
          "Given P(blue) = 2 \u00d7 P(red), so x/(5+x) = 2 \u00d7 5/(5+x).",
          "Multiply both sides by (5+x): x = 10.",
          "Thus, number of blue balls = 10."
        ],
        "derivation": "\\frac{x}{5+x} = 2 \\times \\frac{5}{5+x} \\implies x = 10"
      },
